{
  "title": "Capability-Distributed Resident Intelligence Kernel Model for Deterministic Semantic Operating Systems Based on Interface-Led Architecture",
  "upload_type": "publication",
  "publication_type": "technicalnote",
  "description": "This technical note proposes a capability-distributed resident intelligence kernel model for AIKernel. It separates SeedSLM, a pinned read-only resident intelligence kernel, from DynamicSLM capability modules that are paged into VRAM under deterministic governance. It also defines five-dimensional semantic tensor projection over Telos, Ethos, Logos, Pathos, and Techne, and a Bonsai CTG Router for fail-closed semantic routing. The English manuscript is canonical; the Japanese manuscript is included as a companion translation.",
